HEADWORD: Merchantable
<hw>Mer"chant*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Fit for
market; such as is usually sold in market, or such as will bring the
ordinary price; <as>as, <ex>merchantable</ex> wheat</as>; sometimes, a
technical designation for a particular kind or class.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Merchantly</ent>⟦br⟧
